-- Japan's Nippon Life to raise yen bond holdings in FY2014/15
-- By Shinichi Saoshiro
-- Tue Apr 22, 2014 04:00AM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, April 22 (Reuters) - Japan's Nippon Life Insurance [NPNLI.UL] plans to lift yen bond holdings in the year through March 2015 amid an expected rise in domestic yields and aims to slightly increase unhedged foreign bonds when the yen strengthens, a company official said on Tuesday.

